XSPARQL Lowering README -*- org -*-

* Prerequisite

** Python
You need Python >= 2.4 [[http://www.python.org/]]

** Python Lex-Yacc
[[http://www.dabeaz.com/ply/]]

** XQuery engine
E.g., XQilla [[http://xqilla.sourceforge.net/]], or Saxon
[[http://saxon.sourceforge.net/]]

** SPARQL Endpoint
E.g., Joseki [[http://www.joseki.org/]]

* Installing

Invoke the following command to install xsparqlow:

  $ python setup.py install

See also [[http://docs.python.org/inst/]].

* Running

xsparqlow.py is a rewriter for XSPARQL Lowering to XQuery. You can
transform an XSPARQL file to an XQuery file using the following
command:

  $ cat example.xsparql | xsparqlow.py > out.xquery

Run out.xquery using your favorite XQuery engine.
